com.ibm.jaggr.core.impl.cache

Class ResourceConverterCacheImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.jaggr.core.impl.cache.GenericCacheImpl<com.ibm.jaggr.core.impl.cache.ResourceConverterCacheImpl.CacheEntry>
      • com.ibm.jaggr.core.impl.cache.ResourceConverterCacheImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IGenericCache, IResourceConverterCache, Serializable

    public class ResourceConverterCacheImpl
extends GenericCacheImpl<com.ibm.jaggr.core.impl.cache.ResourceConverterCacheImpl.CacheEntry>
implements Serializable, IResourceConverterCache
    Implementation of a generic cache for resource converters. Clients provide the implementation for converting a resource and writing it to a cache file, and this class handles the management of the cache file in the aggregator cache.

      • convert

        public IResource convert(String key,
                IResource source)
                  throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: IResourceConverterCache
        Returns the cache file for the specified key. If the cache file does not exist, then a new cache file is created by calling the resource converter that was provided in the constructor for this cache instance with the specified source resource.
        Specified by:
        convert in interface IResourceConverterCache
        Parameters:
        key - the cache key
        source - the resource to be converted (may be null). If null, the result will be non-null only if the cache entry already exists.
        Returns:
        the cached resource object, or null if source is null and the cache entry does not already exist.
        Throws:
        IOException
